title: CBT Nuggets - CCNA Data Center DCICN 640-911

This Cisco Data Center video training series with trainer Anthony Sequeira covers Data Center networking technologies and the 640-911 exam.

Recommended skills:
Familiarity with the Windows or MAC operating system
Ability to use the Internet and its related functions such as web browsing and email

Recommended equipment:
While no equipment is required for this course, students could benefit from NX-OS access to practice the various commands demonstrated

In this exciting and important CBT Nugget series, trainer Anthony Sequeira guides learners through the an introduction to Data Center networking technologies, with a particular emphasis on Cisco technologies. This course prepares learners for the 640-911 DCICN exam, which is the first of two exams required for CCNA Data Center.
